## 2026-04-04 - TokenStore file watcher mutations race with route-handler mutations
- Moved the `TokenLock` ownership into `TokenStore` as a public `readonly lock` field. All three watcher callbacks (`change`, `add`, `unlink`) now wrap their `this.sets` mutations and `scheduleRebuild` calls inside `void this.lock.withLock(async () => { ... })`. This serializes external-file-edit callbacks behind any in-progress route handler that already holds the lock, preventing `loadSet()` from overwriting in-flight route mutations.
- In `index.ts`, replaced `const tokenLock = new TokenLock()` with `const tokenLock = tokenStore.lock` so route handlers and watcher callbacks share the exact same promise-chain mutex. No route files required changes.
- Files changed: `packages/server/src/services/token-store.ts` ~L17 (import), ~L39 (lock field), ~L220-250 (watcher callbacks); `packages/server/src/index.ts` ~L67 (lock assignment)

